# Frontend Guide Rules ‚Äî API Documentation

These rules apply when implementing **phase-wise SOW** (as defined by the architect agent in `planning/`). The **agent** must generate concise, structured API documentation for **every endpoint** created or modified in that phase. Documentation lives under `frontend-guide/` and is organized in a Postman-collection style folder structure for easy consumption by frontend developers.

## When to Create/Update Docs

- **For each new endpoint** implemented in a phase: create the corresponding `frontend-guide/apis/{resource}/{action}.md` file.
- **For each modified endpoint** (request/response shape or behavior change): update the existing doc file.
- Create the `apis/{resource}/` folder when adding the first endpoint for that resource.

## Folder Structure (Postman-Collection Style)

- **Base path**: `frontend-guide/apis/`
- **Resource**: one folder per API resource/module (e.g. `auth`, `users`, `projects`), matching route grouping.
- **Action**: one markdown file per HTTP action, **kebab-case** filename.

```
frontend-guide/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ apis/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ login.md
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ register.md
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ refresh-token.md
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ users/
